In a bowl, combine the bread mix, butter, walnuts and egg; mix well. Stir in cranberries. Roll into 1-1/4-in. balls. Place 3 in. apart on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten to 1/8-in. thickness with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-12 minutes or until light golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool.